Recipies

Pan-Seared Pork Chops: pg. 399
	4 (12-oz) bone-in pork rib chops, 1.5 inches thick, trimmed
	salt and pepper
	1-2 tablespoons vegetable oil
	wire rack
	thermometer

Garlic and Thyme Pan Sauce: pg. 400
	1 large shallot, minced
	2 garlic clobes, minced
	0.75 cups low-sodium chicken broth
	0.5 cups dry white win
	1 teaspoon minced fresh thyme
	0.25 teaspoons white wine vinegar
	3 tablespoons unsalted butter, cut into 3 pieces, chilled

Skillet Roasted Potatoes with Garlic and Rosemary: pg 276
	1.5 pounds small red potatoes, cut in half (1.5 - 2 inches in diameter)
	2 tablespoons olive oil
	0.5 teaspoons salt
	0.25 teaspoons pepper
	3 small garlic cloves, minced
	2 teaspoons fresh rosemary, minced

